==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cross-banded
<hw>Cross"-band`ed</hw> <pr>(-b?nd`?d)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>A term
used when a narrow ribbon of veneer is inserted into the surface of any
piece of furniture, wainscoting, etc., so that the grain of it is
contrary to the general surface.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crossbar</ent>⟦br⟧
